      "document_note": "The C4 model for visualizing software architecture emphasizes the importance of clear and effective communication through diagrams. It addresses the challenges faced in accurately representing software architecture and provides a structured approach to creating diagrams at different levels of abstraction. By using System Context, Container, Component, and Code diagrams, developers can effectively communicate the big picture and the finer details of their software systems. The model encourages the use of a shared vocabulary and notation to ensure that architecture diagrams accurately reflect the reality of the software being built."

      "document_note": "This article provides a guide on how to enable dynamic logging levels without application restart for .Net Core apps on the PCF platform using Steeltoe libraries. The article concludes with references and a note from the author."
